Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.65,0:00:04.12,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Alibis, codes, tricks, deals.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.12,0:00:06.19,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The mysterious Black Organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.40,0:00:08.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Today's stage is an old castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.01,0:00:09.78,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Detective Boys' great adventure!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.78,0:00:11.49,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.49,0:00:13.57,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.57,0:00:15.76,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.51,0:01:41.47,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,"Tobuzankei Campsite"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.30,0:01:45.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.41,0:01:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a nice view!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.72,0:01:55.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Come here, hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.88,0:01:58.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why'd we have to come camping with this cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.79,0:02:01.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right. The kids are happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.54,0:02:02.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoa! There's fish!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.89,0:02:04.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.17,0:02:07.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, bring out the tent, doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.38,0:02:11.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tent, the tent...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.38,0:02:14.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.47,0:02:18.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you did something as stupid as forgetting the tent...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.24,0:02:19.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.37,0:02:22.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.75,0:02:24.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.06,0:02:27.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Man, what a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.65,0:02:31.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Going camping while forgetting the most important part—the tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.86,0:02:34.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our vacation just got ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.82,0:02:37.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now it looks like we're lost, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.16,0:02:40.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because you kept butting in while I was trying to figure out directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.90,0:02:45.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems we're gonna have to spend the night in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.07,0:02:47.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.08,0:02:50.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe there's an inn somewhere around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.36,0:02:53.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right! Maybe some sort of castle by the lake?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.04,0:02:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.55,0:02:56.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Doesn't look so ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.31,0:03:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.65,0:03:15.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like a western castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.20,0:03:17.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what's something like this doing in the middle of the woods?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.31,0:03:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure some guy full of cash bought a foreign castle and rebuilt it stone-by-stone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.98,0:03:26.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.56,0:03:27.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.64,0:03:29.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.52,0:03:31.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious? I'm going in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.79,0:03:38.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Where'd you come from, brat? Entering without permission!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.23,0:03:39.71,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Katsuo Tabata (41)\NMamiya Family Gardener
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.11,0:03:44.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, we're not bad people or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.23,0:03:45.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.49,0:03:50.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While we were passing nearby we saw this incredible castle,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.12,0:03:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we were wondering if you wouldn't mind if we could take a look...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.67,0:03:54.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go home, go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.95,0:03:56.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is no place for stra—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.21,0:03:59.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Who are these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.77,0:04:01.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.40,0:04:05.12,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mitsuru Mamiya (49)\NHusband to the Eldest Mamiya Daughter\N(Adopted into the family)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.09,0:04:05.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't remember any planned visits for today...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.12,0:04:08.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That stupid-looking geezer wants to see the inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.54,0:04:10.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who're you calling stupid-looking?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.39,0:04:12.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a brilliant scientist!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.77,0:04:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Scientist?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.48,0:04:15.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.64,0:04:20.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am Hiroshi Agasa, a well-respected inventor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.44,0:04:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, your intelligence...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.94,0:04:26.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...must be far superior to us normal people's, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.91,0:04:28.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.60,0:04:30.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please come inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.47,0:04:33.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you like to stay in the castle for the night?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.35,0:04:35.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! We appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.83,0:04:37.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.43,0:04:40.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think the Mistress would...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.06,0:04:42.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell her they're friends of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.38,0:04:45.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the state my mother-in-law's in, it'll be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.99,0:04:46.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.73,0:04:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.73,0:04:52.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you please let me go?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.06,0:04:53.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.51,0:04:55.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a big garden!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.95,0:05:00.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.61,0:05:01.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.51,0:05:03.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a black one too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.02,0:05:05.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why is it just the head?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.57,0:05:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That horse is a knight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.39,0:05:09.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a chess piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.28,0:05:10.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A chess piece?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.49,0:05:12.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's not just the one piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.46,0:05:14.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the lawn where you're standing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.20,0:05:16.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's in a checkered pattern, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.32,0:05:19.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lawn's cut up like a chess board.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.67,0:05:22.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does someone here like playing chess or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.79,0:05:24.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.29,0:05:28.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've always kept this garden like this as the previous master,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.31,0:05:32.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master Sada'aki instructed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.64,0:05:39.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he too inherited it from the master before, who died 15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.35,0:05:41.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The previous owner...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.20,0:05:43.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then who was that man from before?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.27,0:05:47.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah. He's the Mistress's second husband, Master Mitsuru.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.69,0:05:51.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been here since Master Sada'aki died 6 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.32,0:05:53.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But said Mistress...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.63,0:05:57.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She died in a big fire, four years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.30,0:05:59.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A big fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.25,0:06:01.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, look there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.00,0:06:06.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see the burned tower. That's where the Mistress slept.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.71,0:06:13.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She'd just returned to celebrate her mother's birthday...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.10,0:06:19.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She arrived at midnight, and before dawn, the fire'd already taken over the tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.19,0:06:21.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And not just her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.06,0:06:24.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Several friends she invited,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.14,0:06:29.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the staff who served her mother for years...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.15,0:06:31.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About ten people perished among the flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.18,0:06:37.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only ones who made it were people like me, who'd just been hired,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.84,0:06:41.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,her mother, who'd been in another room due to a cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.84,0:06:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master Mitsuru, since he'd arrived just before the Mistress
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.07,0:06:51.85,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,and the Mistress and Master Sada'aki's only son, Master Takahito.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.75,0:06:57.16,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,0)}Takahito Mamiya (25)\NMamiya Family's Eldest Daughter's Son
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.76,0:06:57.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He arrived two or three days before the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.57,0:07:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From what I understand, he was educated abroad, so it was our first time meeting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.57,0:07:08.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was also the first time we saw Master Mitsuru.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.45,0:07:14.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Mistress apparently married him abroad, and they'd been living there for all that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.54,0:07:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And for some reason, ever since the big fire, Master Takahito has lived here with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.71,0:07:25.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I have a feeling he's obsessed with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.18,0:07:32.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I imagine they weren't accepted into the castle all that well, since nobody even knew their face.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.02,0:07:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. The Mistress sent us photos from when she remarried,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.20,0:07:41.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we all knew how Master Mitsuru looked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.32,0:07:44.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as for Master Takahito, just look.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.07,0:07:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His face is the spitting image of his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.85,0:07:52.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, anyone seeing this can tell they're related.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.89,0:07:56.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what are the other paintings?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.01,0:07:58.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master Sada'aki and the Mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.32,0:08:00.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master Sada'aki was adopted into the family,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.38,0:08:05.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and he had a lot of respect for the owner before him, as they were both historians.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.07,0:08:10.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the Mistress was jealous and always criticized him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.90,0:08:15.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Father was just an argumentative egghead who did nothing but complain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.08,0:08:15.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.70,0:08:17.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.71,0:08:22.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He should've been angry by my words,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.57,0:08:27.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but he was happy that I was honest about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.79,0:08:27.17,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,0)}Masuyo Mamiya (83)\NHead of the Mamiya Family
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.17,0:08:29.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.08,0:08:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to bring back bad memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.20,0:08:33.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.52,0:08:37.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've gotten used to him not being in the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.40,0:08:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like when they changed the size of the passport, or the faces in the bills
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.39,0:08:45.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's odd at first,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.39,0:08:49.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but with time, you come to understand that everything changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.37,0:08:54.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Time is a terrible thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.05,0:08:59.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it erases both happy and sad times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.34,0:09:01.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mistress...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.34,0:09:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.05,0:09:06.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.02,0:09:09.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A scientist friend of the Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.48,0:09:10.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A scientist?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.23,0:09:14.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.13,0:09:20.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then they can uncover the mystery\Nthat he hid in this castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.54,0:09:23.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.02,0:09:26.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Master said it in his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.77,0:09:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That he would leave his greatest treasure to the first one who solved the mystery of the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.20,0:09:36.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, is my daughter home yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.55,0:09:41.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was supposed to come today\Nto celebrate my birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.85,0:09:43.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.21,0:09:44.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mistress...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.23,0:09:49.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell her to come to my room once she arrives. I'm looking forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.05,0:09:51.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since the fire, she's been a bit senile...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.81,0:09:54.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Post-traumatic shock, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.26,0:09:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.52,0:09:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there any room from which you can see the whole chess board?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.98,0:10:02.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chess board in the garden?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.92,0:10:05.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.03,0:10:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chess pieces are all neatly lined up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.49,0:10:10.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where? I don't see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.40,0:10:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't push, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.62,0:10:16.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see them from this room, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.00,0:10:16.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.63,0:10:26.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Does the pieces' layout mean anything, or...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.59,0:10:28.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're happy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.87,0:10:32.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's one of those codes you love so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.36,0:10:34.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.32,0:10:36.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I think so, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.56,0:10:38.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.00,0:10:40.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?! You're gonna fall!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.23,0:10:42.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those morons!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.82,0:10:46.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think you're doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.68,0:10:50.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I was gonna fall...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.19,0:10:53.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now he fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.38,0:10:55.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.75,0:10:56.49,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.49,0:10:59.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The window's right next to the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.02,0:11:03.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but in the other room, it was too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.11,0:11:08.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then what's between the two windows?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.06,0:11:27.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}After all, since the old times it's been said...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.12,0:11:30.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...just match up the clock's hands and...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.24,0:11:35.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.62,0:11:37.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was here just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.07,0:11:40.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.82,0:11:43.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This ain't no normal castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.49,0:11:47.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is starting to get interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.59,0:11:50.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A staircase...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.65,0:11:53.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is pretty deep...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.51,0:11:56.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Where do these stairs continue to?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.73,0:12:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.44,0:12:12.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.36,0:12:14.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wasn't he in the other room just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.87,0:12:15.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.95,0:12:18.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I looked the other way, and suddenly he was gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.84,0:12:20.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.03,0:12:22.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The chair fell down and the books are scattered...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.75,0:12:24.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The clock's lid is open...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.65,0:12:25.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the clock has been changed...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.10,0:12:37.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.91,0:12:40.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.19,0:12:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.11,0:12:47.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't do bad things.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.88,0:12:51.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did the kids do something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.30,0:12:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, just a little prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.67,0:12:54.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Prank?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.50,0:12:58.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} disappeared, so we're trying to find him!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.35,0:13:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.31,0:13:02.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must've gone to the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.36,0:13:04.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's right under here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.21,0:13:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.16,0:13:09.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he was going to the toilet, he should've told us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.62,0:13:11.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ugh...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.69,0:13:16.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? That's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.16,0:13:18.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nobody here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.25,0:13:20.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there any other toilet?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.25,0:13:24.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This place isn't used that much, so just this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.37,0:13:29.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he hid somewhere and wants to scare us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.29,0:13:33.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has to be that. Sometimes Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} can be so childish...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.72,0:13:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.99,0:13:37.47,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You're children too...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.47,0:13:40.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master Takahito, dinner's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.42,0:13:42.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's dinner time already?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.93,0:13:46.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had them make dinner for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.00,0:13:46.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Want to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.75,0:13:48.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grilled eel?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.65,0:13:51.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if we don't look for Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.36,0:13:53.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.01,0:13:56.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'll probably come out when he's hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.78,0:14:00.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the food!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.84,0:14:04.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it nice sometimes\Nfor it to be cheerful like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.50,0:14:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since my mother died, less and less people come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.33,0:14:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did you two move here after the fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.30,0:14:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd long planned to come live here after I was done with the university.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.78,0:14:28.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was worried about my mother-in-law, since she lost her only daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.54,0:14:34.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I've come to love the castle my wife was born in more and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.23,0:14:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What you like isn't the castle,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.24,0:14:41.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's the treasure hidden somewhere inside it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.45,0:14:43.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandmother...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.20,0:14:45.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe so.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.81,0:14:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't deny that my father-in-law's will {\i1}does{\i0} influence my being here...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.04,0:14:57.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmph. It's hard to believe my daughter could fall for such a greedy man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.09,0:14:59.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll take dinner in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.08,0:15:03.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When my daughter arrives, tell her to meet me there. I have much to tell her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.51,0:15:08.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As usual, Grandmother acts as if Mother was still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.50,0:15:11.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that her memory's bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.20,0:15:16.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since she broke her legs ten years ago, she never left the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.73,0:15:20.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, have you solved the mystery, Agasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.19,0:15:20.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.93,0:15:24.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? You haven't heard about it yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.16,0:15:32.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Father said he'd leave his greatest treasure to the first one to figure the mystery of the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.42,0:15:36.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I heard about that from the gardener, Tabata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.42,0:15:39.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't even know where to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.07,0:15:42.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chess pieces in the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.43,0:15:47.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that chess board was arranged by the same person who hid the treasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.95,0:15:52.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then the position of the pieces must be a hint to find the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.44,0:15:54.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.45,0:15:58.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really think so, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.19,0:16:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you have figured out their meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.26,0:16:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.42,0:16:08.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You couldn't solve it even though you've had four years.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.82,0:16:12.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one who could do it is lost somewhere in the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.83,0:16:16.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That mystery gourmet full of vigor and curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.35,0:16:17.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.56,0:16:18.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mystery...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.83,0:16:20.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...gourmet?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.25,0:16:23.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here. Will this do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.02,0:16:23.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.50,0:16:27.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you want that bag for?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.72,0:16:31.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to save one of my pieces of bread for Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.83,0:16:35.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he'll be hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.98,0:16:39.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, what happened to the boy with the glasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.04,0:16:42.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We haven't seen him in quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.55,0:16:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll set out to find him once we finish dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.46,0:16:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This castle's kind of like a maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.36,0:16:52.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he got lost somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.00,0:16:54.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just hope he didn't end up in that tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.91,0:16:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"That tower?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.12,0:16:59.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, that tower to the left of the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.91,0:17:07.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's covered in vegetation ever since my wife burned to death in it, four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.25,0:17:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. Also, two years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.45,0:17:16.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,an employee we'd just hired mysteriously disappeared one night.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.10,0:17:19.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking about him, it seems that he used to say that there was something
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.83,0:17:22.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,odd about that tower to the employees he was close to,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.73,0:17:24.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and so we searched for him there,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.80,0:17:29.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and though there were signs someone had been there recently, we couldn't find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.07,0:17:34.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterward we called the police, and they began a big search of the entire woods...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.53,0:17:36.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what happened after?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.92,0:17:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ten days later...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.90,0:17:42.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was finally found in the woods...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.96,0:17:44.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...having died from starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.56,0:17:47.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.40,0:17:49.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.40,0:17:52.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police concluded that he'd gotten lost in the woods,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.31,0:17:56.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in an unfortunate accident, but among the staff,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.77,0:18:00.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a mysterious rumor was told for quite a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.27,0:18:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the souls of those that died in the tower had possessed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.82,0:18:10.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since then, the entrance to the tower is sealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.78,0:18:15.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we have to hurry and find Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} before he starves!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.49,0:18:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll save my bread for him, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.00,0:18:19.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.45,0:18:24.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, let's split into groups and find him before it's too dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.17,0:18:26.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.38,0:18:28.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.17,0:18:30.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're hiding, come out!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.43,0:18:34.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He doesn't seem to be in the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.75,0:18:38.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We looked for him inside the castle, but we couldn't find him anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.35,0:18:40.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he might be in that tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.77,0:18:41.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.98,0:18:43.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We checked the entrance just now,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.98,0:18:46.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the door is still locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.57,0:18:50.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then all that's left is the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.03,0:18:52.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's raining pretty hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.84,0:18:55.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Entering the woods at night is dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.65,0:19:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It may be wiser to wait until the morning, then have the police search for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.00,0:19:03.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, you guys, get back to your rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.10,0:19:06.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.60,0:19:07.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.73,0:19:10.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.05,0:19:12.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.05,0:19:14.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about Edogawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.94,0:19:16.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's not a weak man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.64,0:19:20.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He can find a way out of wherever he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.46,0:19:28.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of crying, how about you tie that bag so the bread doesn't get wet from the rain?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.32,0:19:29.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.16,0:19:31.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're going to catch a cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.03,0:19:32.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.92,0:19:34.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.98,0:19:38.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you know Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} so well?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.11,0:19:40.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.13,0:19:42.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.25,0:19:45.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that you {\i1}like{\i0} Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.02,0:19:55.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.65,0:19:58.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.65,0:20:00.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.91,0:20:04.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't see him that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.88,0:20:08.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.02,0:20:10.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? For real?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.36,0:20:15.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez. Kids these days...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.45,0:20:19.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's as you say, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.\NShin'ichi's probably all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.50,0:20:22.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As they say, "no news is good news."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.67,0:20:25.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You actually bought that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.13,0:20:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you really think he'd let us worry for so long without contacting us?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.60,0:20:35.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something happened to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.26,0:20:39.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe somebody in this castle kidnapped him, and he can't find a way out,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.80,0:20:41.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,or in the worst-case scenario...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.00,0:20:44.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.72,0:20:46.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.72,0:20:50.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, we have to call the police without the owners of the castle finding out,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.71,0:20:53.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and continue investigating.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.07,0:20:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. We have to search for him, not in the woods,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.23,0:20:58.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but inside the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.08,0:21:00.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I have an idea where to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.16,0:21:02.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Snap out of it, doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.20,0:21:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With him gone, you're the only adult we can count on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.50,0:21:16.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.24,0:21:19.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Phone... phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.68,0:21:23.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.44,0:21:38.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Shin'ichi's cap!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.53,0:21:42.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with this door?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.65,0:21:46.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.83,0:21:56.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doctor? If you're going to call someone,\Ncall someone who knows us,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.14,0:21:59.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,like Detective Yokomizo, or Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.54,0:22:03.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.90,0:22:07.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doctor...?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.18,0:23:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then what about Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.29,0:23:55.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have fallen into the hands of the one following us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.21,0:23:57.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.05,0:23:58.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's {\i1}not{\i0} Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.50,0:24:01.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s glasses...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.98,0:24:05.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the culprit's aim was this castle's treasure...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.57,0:24:15.54,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.54,0:24:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Passport Size
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.25,0:24:22.98,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next episode, the culprit is an unexpected person!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.98,0:24:25.40,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's who it is, I've decided that's who it is.
